The fox was persistent, Cody had to give it that. Biting back a squeal of agony, Cody dropped the remains of the glass
bottle and reached back into his bag. His questing fingers brushed past his camera. "Good enough," he said, brought it
out, and snapped a picture of the fox. The flash nearly blinded Cody, and the fox, who was on the receiving end, let
go of his leg with a doleful whine.
